<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="77" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,151,968]" pageId="14" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,439,464]" pageId="14" pageNumber="77">Comments.</emphasis>
This species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1805" box="[680,816,441,464]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Tabanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivittatus">
<emphasis box="[680,816,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="77">T. trivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Carmo &amp; Henriques, 2019" authorityName="Carmo &amp; Henriques" authorityYear="2019" box="[869,1027,441,464]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Tabanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocerus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[869,1027,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="77">T. macrocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1035,1097,439,464]" pageId="14" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1035,1097,439,464]" pageId="14" pageNumber="77" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, separated from the former by the somewhat paler integument, mid and hind coxae and femora. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carmo &amp; Henriques" authorityYear="2019" box="[1049,1204,476,501]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Tabanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mackerrasi">
<emphasis box="[1049,1204,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="77">T. mackerrasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from 
<taxonomicName authority="Carmo &amp; Henriques, 2019" authorityName="Carmo &amp; Henriques" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Tabanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macrocerus" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="77">T. macrocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[291,356,511,536]" pageId="14" pageNumber="77">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[291,356,511,536]" pageId="14" pageNumber="77" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
by the dark notopleuron, concolorous with adjacent scutum, some specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Carmo &amp; Henriques" authorityYear="2019" box="[1281,1436,511,536]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Tabanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mackerrasi">
<emphasis box="[1281,1436,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="77">T. mackerrasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also have a black integumental stripe ventrally at the abdomen, however this character is variable. Despite of using only one character, we decided to propose these as two species, since the character in question, the pattern of coloration of the notopleuron with relation to the notum, is a character traditionally used to delimitate species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1805" box="[151,260,657,680]" class="Insecta" family="Tabanidae" genus="Tabanus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="trivittatus">
<emphasis box="[151,260,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="77">trivittatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Fairchild, G. B." box="[349,520,655,680]" pageId="14" pageNumber="77" pagination="237 - 261" refId="ref17120" refString="Fairchild, G. B. (1976) Notes on Neotropical Tabanidae (Dipt.) XVI. The Tabanus trivittatus complex. Studia Entomologica, 19 (1 - 4), 237 - 261." type="journal article" year="1976">Fairchild 1976</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Gorayeb, I. S. &amp; Rafael, J. A." box="[533,810,655,680]" pageId="14" pageNumber="77" pagination="45 - 55" refId="ref17481" refString="Gorayeb, I. S. &amp; Rafael, J. A. (1984) Tabanidae (Dipt.) da Amazonia. V. Descricao de duas especies novas. Boletim do Museu Paraense Emilio Goeldi, serie Zoologia, 7 (1), 45 - 55." type="journal article" year="1984">Gorayeb &amp; Rafael 1984</bibRefCitation>
), being a crucial character in the key. Further evidence may show this three species, to be the same taxon or a complex of several species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
